# Cursor Rule Management

## When to Add/Update Rules

**Add new rule when:**
- Pattern used in 3+ files
- Common bug preventable by rule
- Repeated code review feedback
- New library/tool adopted project-wide

**Update existing rule when:**
- Better examples exist in codebase
- New edge cases discovered
- Implementation changed

**Deprecate when:**
- Pattern no longer used
- Technology replaced

## Rule Format

### Frontmatter
```markdown
---
description: One-line description of rule purpose
globs: path/to/files/*.ext, other/**/*
---
```

### Content Structure
- **Bold main points**
  - Sub-points with details
  - DO/DON'T examples from actual code
  - Cross-reference related rules (no duplication)

### File References
- Rules: `[prisma.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/prisma.mdc)`
- Code: `[schema.prisma](mdc:prisma/schema.prisma)`

### Code Examples
```typescript
// ✅ DO: Correct pattern
const good = true;

// ❌ DON'T: Anti-pattern
const bad = false;
```

## Quality Standards
- Actionable and specific (not vague)
- Examples from actual codebase
- Consistent formatting
- Up-to-date references

**Action**: When you see a pattern 3+ times, immediately suggest adding it to the appropriate rule.